  "text": "Once upon a matchday — it was the semi-final, on the 15th of July 2026 — two teams walked out under the soft evening lights. Argentina turned it around in the final minutes to reach the final and defend their crown. England chased a first final since 1966; Argentina chased back-to-back World Cups. The margin was Lionel Messi.\n\nIn the 55th minute, Anthony Gordon sent the ball gently home, and the score whispered 1–0. In the 85th minute, Enzo Fernández sent the ball gently home, and the score whispered 1–1. In the 92nd minute, Lautaro Martínez sent the ball gently home, and the score whispered 1–2.\n\nAnthony Gordon's early second-half strike had England ahead and daring to dream. Then Messi took over as creator: Enzo Fernández levelled with a fine strike from distance in the 85th minute. Three minutes into stoppage time, substitute Lautaro Martínez headed the winner from another pinpoint Messi cross to break English hearts. England will rue how much they gave Messi to work with; against him, small margins are rarely survived.\n\nAnd so the story ended England 1–2 Argentina. Argentina carried on their long journey, and England lay down to rest. Every goal in this tale is a true one — kept safe and provable on the blockchain by TxLINE — so you can close your eyes knowing not a single fact was ever made up. Sleep well, and goodnight.",
